      "updated": 1780989218415,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "-> rest operator work as when we we give values to a function then it will give it as a array.\n\nfunction addValue(...nums){\n    console.log(nums);\n}\n\nconsole.log(addValue(1,2,3,4,5,6,7));\n\n--> rest operator use in project.\n\nfunction total(...prices){\n\n}\n\nfunction mergeUsers(...users){\n\n}\n\n-> spread operator work as when we give values in form of array it will spread them.\n\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "-> rest operator work as when we we give values to a function then it will give it as a array.\n\nfunction addValue(...nums){\n    console.log(nums);\n}\n\nconsole.log(addValue(1,2,3,4,5,6,7));\n\n--> rest operator use in project.\n\nfunction total(...prices){\n\n}\n\nfunction mergeUsers(...users){\n\n}\n\n-> spread operator work as when we give values in form of array it will spread them.\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
